embeds.title: Historical Stat Tracking Info Page
embeds.description:
- The `/daily`, `/weekly`, `/monthly`, and `/yearly` commands show your current stats for the respective time periods. They reflect your performance in the ongoing day, week, month, or year.
- The `/last` commands show your previous stats for the respective time periods. They summarize your performance in the completed day, week, month, or year.
- The `/difference` commands group show the difference in your stats for the respective time periods. They compare your performance in the current day, week, month, or year to the previous one.
- Adding a number after the `/last` commands shows the stats of a specific past period. For example, /lastweek 2 shows the stats of two weeks ago.
